On Tuesday, U.S. Rep. Chellie Pingree, D-Maine, [shared](https://bsky.app/profile/pingree.house.gov/post/3mcctcaa7zk2v) a photo of Department of Homeland Security Secretary Kristi Noem [speaking at a news conference](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RWFMXDstB7s).

The Homeland Security-branded podium Noem stood behind included the words, “One of ours. All of yours,” a phrase that some online [started to link](https://www.masslive.com/entertainment/2026/01/rock-legend-accuses-trump-administration-of-using-nazi-mass-murder-slogan.html) to [fascism](https://brendonbeebe.substack.com/p/one-of-ours-all-of-yours-origins) and Nazis [murdering residents of a Czech village](https://www.lidice-memorial.cz/en/memorial/memorial-and-reverent-area/history-of-the-village-lidice/#:~:text=340%20Lidice%20citizens%20were%20murdered%20by%20the%20Nazis%2C%20143%20Lidice%20women%20returned%20home%20after%20the%20war%20ended%2C%20and%20after%20a%20two%2Dyear%20search%2017%20children%20were%20restored%20to%20their%20mothers.) during World War II.

“Even if Noem has no idea what this means, the fact that \*anyone\* in the Admin would put a Nazi slogan on public display is incredibly alarming—and points to the moral rot at the heart of DHS,” Pingree wrote.

